<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-25T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-25T17:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3553: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Des Partes</hi></persName>)<note n="31" xml:id="d79fn31">The same telegram, February 25, 5 p.m.,
                                    to the Minister in Paraguay as No. 8.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-25T17:00:00-05:00">February 25, 1934—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3. The Department has been advised by the League Chaco Commission of
                                the formula of solution delivered by it to the Governments of
                                Bolivia and Paraguay on February 22. Please cable immediately the
                                fullest information available as to the attitude of the Government
                                to which you are accredited regarding the proposal offered.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>